<paragraph id="ADDF2D986EF11A5CD054870415742DCE" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">
<taxonomicName id="B39F8D4DB86B5F6CC5A707AC71DA71F6" authority="Retz." class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="489" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oederi">
Carex 
<normalizedToken id="337EC107404522EC8BC914A64004D1CF" originalValue="Oedéri" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Oederi</normalizedToken>
Retz.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="73F0611713EF11D10084FF038C1D899A" pageId="null" pageNumber="489" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="1C04EB8A948DEA063DB42F8D1B07C316" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Oeders Segge</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="4730D24380F6A2096A775AD5FC6ABC7D" pageId="null" pageNumber="489" type="description">
<paragraph id="6667358F0054CF96944FCB63F04B1EE0" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">
5-20 cm hoch. 
<normalizedToken id="419D700B6D8C41FEAC0812FEEA03D1A7" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
1,5-3 mm breit, 
<emphasis id="E8299300B0EEE937B160D25A9BBBC14A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">
rinnig gefaltet, 
<normalizedToken id="01AEF4A26AEB8EBDAFC72CA27EB9FFA2" originalValue="gelbgrün" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">gelbgruen</normalizedToken>
oder 
<normalizedToken id="BC71FBC00FC899C46DB9EAAD3E205C4A" originalValue="grün" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">gruen</normalizedToken>
.
</emphasis>
Stengel steif aufrecht. 
<normalizedToken id="894B66D3597E146E978147D9C2FE13FC" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
1,5-3 cm lang, aus 3-6 meist 
<emphasis id="F09B669422576BEBBD6BE0C861B77DED" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">
<normalizedToken id="0EF0066BCFEBF1C5B4B3428FD23EAE7D" originalValue="gedrängt" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">gedraengt</normalizedToken>
stehenden
</emphasis>
, sitzenden, zylindrischen oder kugeligen, 0,5-1 cm langen und 0,3-0,6 cm dicken ♀ 
<normalizedToken id="B33A876AF38BF8C0C9B3270FAD97DED4" originalValue="Ähren" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Aehren</normalizedToken>
; Stiel 
<emphasis id="ABCF84A0AA4083FFB92A817A2498092F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">der</emphasis>
♂ 
<emphasis id="8A8FF20793E8E36295901C4D84F191FF" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">
<normalizedToken id="0BE24948EE27445B94D9B03BEADF0622" originalValue="Ähre" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Aehre</normalizedToken>
die
</emphasis>
♀ 
<emphasis id="577882197D213292421809C82F1DEECE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">
<normalizedToken id="84EDC60071394022B5E409A5B9F77BF9" originalValue="Ähren" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Aehren</normalizedToken>
nicht 
<normalizedToken id="29C929A966579159477909F665844E55" originalValue="überragend" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">ueberragend</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="3978182FEE5ED4279FE079220285FA35" originalValue="Fruchtschläuche" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Fruchtschlaeuche</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm lang, gerade
</emphasis>
, meist 
<normalizedToken id="2B2886F6D5E03FB337B448D56455F4E5" originalValue="plötzlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">ploetzlich</normalizedToken>
in den Schnabel 
<normalizedToken id="2CC07AF9773E94D20F41264211F17E4C" originalValue="verschmälert" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">verschmaelert</normalizedToken>
; 
<emphasis id="254BE2B4FDAABC37E0094EECDB10C0E8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">
Frucht den Fruchtschlauch nicht 
<normalizedToken id="6C924A046ED48BB01E053B6899BBD27A" originalValue="ausfüllend" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">ausfuellend</normalizedToken>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="68B977A7AF2D6FC6DE1647EC59EE77F2" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">
<emphasis id="B62696337A0433821E8BF8A0FA2A8F62" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="18FA24B173F3E441FDAB75F6190ECB24" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">70:</emphasis>
(Tanaka aus Tischler 1950), Material aus England, Irland und Schweden (Davies 1955Davies 1956a), aus Island (
<normalizedToken id="3AE68D3A1351DBD221A36395CD47F968" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Loeve</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="2334EA3317B34F40F454428536836BCB" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Loeve</normalizedToken>
1956b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6A2B3517AEA15D0F5CD125B16F3032D3" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">
<emphasis id="644AD3DE310579CC4F969DFAC82DC942" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin, montan und subalpin. Nasse, schlammige oder torfige, seltener sandige und lehmige, kalkfreie und kalkhaltige 
<normalizedToken id="E4EF3C759A16462AE5C1695980C17BB8" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Boeden</normalizedToken>
. Flach- und Hochmoore.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C3642FE275A04E21AADA9ED55E6F511B" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">
<emphasis id="0072E0EE08FFECB677F1C753A18D78A1" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Verbreitung. Eurasiatische Pflanze:</emphasis>
Ganz 
<taxonomicName id="45EB3487E735946F82199180D4AD4A90" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Europa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Europa</taxonomicName>
; Sibirien (
<normalizedToken id="7CD22C2FF5D8088E3994954EDE2FB8FD" originalValue="ostwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">ostwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Baikalseegebiet), Turkestan, Iran; Nordwestafrika; Angaben aus Nordamerika zweifelhaft; nach Nelmes (1955) auch Belege aus Neuseeland. - Im Gebiet verbreitet, nicht 
<normalizedToken id="6203752125DBA7A3362FE9D58CAAA62D" originalValue="häufig" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">haeufig</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="549B0908C85EC401B4A0268E8FEAF652" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">
<emphasis id="146EC771750D2B3317E9C73371B55ACB" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Bemerkungen.</emphasis>
Untersuchungen im Herbar von Retzius haben ergeben, 
<normalizedToken id="CA48F156ECBC697C7913CFBBAAA2C532" originalValue="daß" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">dass</normalizedToken>
Retzius 
<taxonomicName id="7EE67A6340410AED8EC3FC4360A528C2" authority="L." authorityName="L." class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="489" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pilulifera">
<emphasis id="18B635DAC8C717BD1D73BED7B624B0F8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">C. pilulifera</emphasis>
<authorityName id="13F0FF362C0D4DCAB062CB62D1B2DC6D" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">L.</authorityName>
</taxonomicName>
als 
<taxonomicName id="6B8E20EFBC50258A9279F853EFC9FB49" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="489" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oederi">
<emphasis id="951F660300E184C6DDB7C8A3E11D68E2" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">C. Oederi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bezeichnet hat; 
<taxonomicName id="04A37523198B1DE8FEEF0A505166784E" authority="Retz." authorityName="Retz." class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="489" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oederi">
<emphasis id="68C94EAAFC5DDEBB3ADC928513AD7400" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">C. Oederi</emphasis>
Retz.
</taxonomicName>
ist also Synonym von 
<taxonomicName id="B34608B942857DDC98D146FA7A9240C4" authority="L. Bisher" authorityName="L. Bisher" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="489" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pilulifera">
<emphasis id="0C322F2556302A4316A6524173FF2CAE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">C. pilulifera</emphasis>
<authorityName id="02857F0C58B89CA7308C970FB94532C1" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">L.</authorityName>
Bisher
</taxonomicName>
hat dies aber nie 
<normalizedToken id="A72E103C05904E9896EB34BEE5A98471" originalValue="Anlaß" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Anlass</normalizedToken>
zu Verwechslungen gegeben, da unter 
<taxonomicName id="C36960D12BA7679463843586AEC07A44" authority="Retz." authorityName="Retz." class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="489" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oederi">
<emphasis id="0634219C1447047F3E744D32CB372532" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">C. Oederi</emphasis>
Retz.
</taxonomicName>
stets diese Art aus der 
<emphasis id="D823144A5398DA37AAC3E55B4DD99A87" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">C. flava-</emphasis>
Gruppe verstanden wurde. Anstelle von 
<taxonomicName id="7FE3C6590C55D82F21B092595BF7BC5F" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="489" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oederi">
<emphasis id="652C764EA55B5C44BADF72802F87B117" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">C. Oederi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
soll nun der Name 
<taxonomicName id="8AFFFAC74D1EBD46DF10E75B46957437" authority="Merat" authorityName="Merat" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cleistogenes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="489" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serotina">
<emphasis id="CD5B15426C296DDCEA168EF07AD7EBAE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">C. serotina</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="09DF34CA5538BDBAB01F614F7D96B471" originalValue="Mérat" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">Merat</normalizedToken>
</taxonomicName>
gelten. Wir schlagen vor, den Namen 
<taxonomicName id="1DED4EEA16964B62919C5CE8DD2469D1" authority="Retz." authorityName="Retz." class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="489" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oederi">
<emphasis id="90521F764DC38CCF28473A6B4A9D8315" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="489">C. Oederi</emphasis>
Retz.
</taxonomicName>
beizubehalten.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
